  "texts": [
    "Concisely, the primary contributions of this paper are enumerated below: (5) Essential Technical Innovations in DL for Paleontological Research: The review discusses breakthrough innovations from the mainstream computer vision and natural language processing domains that could be adopted to solve the limitations of existing studies and gaps in the literature.",
    "Specifically, this work includes discussion/recommendations on image augmentation methodologies, image enhancement approaches, and novel neural network architectures and paradigms.The remainder of this review is structured as follows: In Sect. 2, we outline the systematic approach adopted for the review, detailing the article search strategy, study selection criteria, and the protocols for data extraction from the selected papers.",
    "The Sect. 3 provides a historical perspective on fossil image analysis, transitioning from traditional methods to highlighting the growing potential of DL in micropaleontology.",
    "This section also covers the necessary background for DL required for a complete understanding of the studies included in this survey.",
    "The subsequent Sect. 4, exhaustively reviews the studies in literature, covering their novelty and limitations while simultaneously tabulating key results and takeaway remarks."
